  <Subject Subject_ID="300047910">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300191091</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>visual works by material or technique [300191091], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Contemporary works of art that employ several distinct art forms, such as sculpture and music or painting and light art. For the concept that certain contemporary works merge known art forms to inaugurate a new type, use "intermedia." To indicate that works are composed of a variety of materials, use "mixed media."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para obras de arte del siglo XX que emplean distintas formas de arte, tales como escultura y música o pintura y arte cinético. Para el concepto que ciertas obras del siglo XX que unen formas de arte conocido para inaugurar un nuevo tipo, use "intermedia". Para indicar aquellas obras que son compuestas de una variedad de materiales, use "medio mixto".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>20e-eeuwse kunstwerken die gebruik maken van verscheidene duidelijk te onderscheiden kunstvormen, zoals de beeldhouwkunst en muziek of de schilderkunst en lichtkunst. Voor het concept dat bepaalde 20e eeuwse werken bekende kunstvormen laten samenvloeien voor een nieuwe soort kunst wordt 'intermedia' gebruikt. Gebruik 'gemengde media' om werken aan te duiden die bestaan uit een verscheidenheid aan materialen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>運用數種不同的藝術形式，例如雕塑和音樂或繪畫和光線藝術，所創作而出的當代藝術作品。若指將某些當代作品融入已知的藝術形式，藉以開展一種新藝術型態的概念，使用「互媒體」一詞。而若指由多種媒材所組合而成的作品，則使用「綜合媒體」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zeitgenössisches Kunstwerk, das verschiedene unterschiedliche Kunstformen verwendet, wie Skulptur und Musik oder Malerei und Lichtkunst. Für das Konzept, dass bestimmte zeitgenössische Arbeiten bekannte Kunstformen verbinden, um einen neuen Typ einzuführen, siehe "Intermedia." Um anzugeben, dass Arbeiten aus einer Vielzahl von Materialien zusammengefügt sind, ist "Mixed Media" zu verwenden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
